m0:BicephalousPerspective a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Bicephalous Perspective Integration" ;
    rdfs:comment "Synthesis of Eagle Eye (ASFID — Territory) and Sphinx Eye (REVOI — Map) perspectives for the I Ching as SymbolicSystemGrammar." .

m0:HexagramCombination a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Hexagram (二卦) — Symbolic Combination" ;
    rdfs:comment "A hexagram is a unique 6-line symbolic signature formed by stacking two trigrams. 64 hexagrams = 8 × 8 exhaustive combinations. Each hexagram occupies a unique position in the 6-dimensional binary space {Yin,Yang}⁶ and receives 4 layers of traditional interpretation." .

m0:SSGValidation a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "SymbolicSystemGrammar Validation" ;
    rdfs:comment "Validation of the I Ching's status as a SymbolicSystemGrammar instance: finite primitives, combination rules, multiple legitimate interpretations, symbolic arbitration." .

m0:M2Candidates a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "M2 Candidate Metaconcepts" ;
    rdfs:comment "Potential new M2 metaconcepts identified through I Ching analysis, requiring cross-domain validation before M2 inclusion." .

m0:Primitive a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Primitive (Elementary Line)" ;
    rdfs:comment "The two indivisible atomic elements of the I Ching grammar: Yang (undivided line) and Yin (divided line). All higher structures are composed exclusively from these two primitives via stacking rules." .

m0:GrammarRule a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Grammar Rule" ;
    rdfs:comment "Formal combinatorial rule governing the construction of higher symbolic structures from lower-level elements." .

m0:SemanticLayer a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Semantic Layer (Interpretation Layer)" ;
    rdfs:comment "One of the four traditional interpretive layers applied to each hexagram. Together they constitute the interpretive grammar — the rules for extracting meaning from symbolic combinations." .

m0:TrigramPolarities a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Trigram Polarity Pairs" ;
    rdfs:comment "The 8 trigrams form 4 polarity pairs (nuclear opposites). Each pair shares the same binary code inverted — maximal symbolic distance within the grammar." .

m0:ASFIDAnalysis a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "ASFID Analysis (Eagle Eye — Territory Perspective)" ;
    rdfs:comment "Five-dimensional measurement of the I Ching as an observable symbolic system: Attractor, Structure, Flow, Information, Dynamics." .

m0:REVOIAnalysis a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "REVOI Analysis (Sphinx Eye — Map Perspective)" ;
    rdfs:comment "Five-dimensional evaluation of the I Ching as a conceptual map: Representability, Evolvability, Verifiability, Observability, Interoperability." .

m0:M2MetaconceptActivation a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "M2 Metaconcept Activation" ;
    rdfs:comment "M2 metaconcepts instantiated or validated by the I Ching as SymbolicSystemGrammar." .

m0:Trigram a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Trigram (Archetype)" ;
    rdfs:comment "One of the 8 fundamental symbolic archetypes of the I Ching. Each trigram is a named 3-line pattern corresponding to a natural phenomenon, a family role, a body part, a compass direction, and a quality of energy. Trigrams are the reusable building blocks (archetypes) that combine to form all 64 hexagrams." .

